review_data: Reviewed in the United States on June 29, 2023
name: AFD
title: 5.0 out of 5 starsTons of screws. Patience and a power screwdriver or drill will go a long way.
review: Box comes with everything you need. The assembled product looks great and feels sturdy. A great value for the price. However, three key points: 1) The kit comes with four panels marked P1 and two end panels marked P2. They look the same but there's a slight size difference. If you don't put the P2s on the ends, the box will look off. 2) The kit has a small bag packed with screws and wingnuts. The bag is made of the thinnest plastic imaginable, a value engineering marvel no doubt, so the weight of the screws and nuts may tear it causing these bits to end up all over the the box. Beware when opening. 3) The screws are not the greatest quality, which is fine for this price point. Hand-screw the wingnuts on a couple of spins before tightening with any power tool or you will strip the threads right away.
